// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL4-5_Task_03 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecurityTerminalDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1034077255" "Welcome. Full security clearance has been granted. Please specify your desired action."
// Answer Text :
"P4231621757" "Access confidential files on Archon Dimitri"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1198667921" "Archon Dimitri is the leader of Company 227 of the Council initiative. Archon Dimitri is currently reported to be developing an advanced Vampyri Super Soldier program that has, so far, shown extremely promising results, with Dimitri using himself as a test bed for the technology. Nosferatu has applauded Dimitri's efforts publicly within the Council. Archon Dimitri has proven to be an example to his troops and is commended on his dedication to the Council's initiatives."
// Answer Text :
"P3789512485" "Investigate new technology for Vampyri Super Soldiers"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P2180826448" "<color orange>You discover archival video of Archon Dimitri demonstrating the new technology he has researched. He refers to it as Project: Bloodpool.<br><br>In the video you see the contorted and stretched facial features of the grotesque Archon Dimitri as he stands before a stasis tube in which floats an unconscious figure bristling with hoses and wires. Dimitri speaks.</color><br><br>"I have developed this new technology, dubbed Project: Bloodpool, that will enable the Council to turn the power of our enemies against them."<br><br><color orange>Archon Dimitri turns and walks back to stand beside the stasis tube, placing his hand upon the glass.</color><br><br>"This is subject 7, a member of Freedom Corps my agents captured last week. His powers are... crude, but will suffice for the purposes of this demonstration. Project: Bloodpool builds upon the Vampyri Super Soldier program perfected by the brilliant Nosferatu, myself one of the successes of his program. In this demonstration I shall return the favor, and utilize my own body as the testbed for my technology. When the machine is activated, Subject 7's powers shall be transfered to myself, boosting my strength and toughness beyond their already exceptional levels."<br><br><color orange>The Archon inserts a single tube into each side of his neck and one into his chest, just over his heart and then nods to someone offscreen. With a strobe of light and a swarm of bubbles, the subject in the stasis tube is wracked with energy, convulsing as electricity arcs from electrodes along the outside of the tube. Within seconds Archon Dimitri surges with power, a visible glow radiating from his eyes, nose, and mouth. With an audible change to his voice he yells over the cacophony for them to disengage the device.</color><br><br>"Turn it off..."<br><br><color orange>The flashing light ceases, the bubbles disperse, and subject 7 ceases his convulsions. Over the next few seconds the light from Dimitri's eyes, nose and mouth fades and he removes the tubes from his body. He motions off screen, beckoning someone, and a Council soldier struggles to drag a bundle of 12, two inch thick lengths of steel rebar to the Archon. Dimitri steps forward, seizing the bundle with one hand and swatting the peon out of the frame. He lifts the bundle like it was a toy sword, grips it with his other hand, and bends, then snaps the bundle in half. Steel splinters spray into the air and bounce harmlessly off of Dimitri, who drops the bundle with a deafening clatter against the concrete floor of the facility. Dimitri speaks.</color><br><br>"The effects are currently unstable, and only last for a matter of hours. The drain on the subjects is significant, and death is certain after five to nine uses. I am currently working on a way to limit the drain so that subjects do not need to be replaced regularly. With a large enough pool of subjects, the lower overall boost should even out with sustainability. This is my current focus; increasing reliability and sustainability of the system, and I am currently gathering additional subjects from the ranks of Freedom Corps. Thank you for your consideration.""
// Answer Text :
"P2923237815" "What is the status of Dimitri's advancements?"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P2220649284" "Archon Dimitri has increased sustainability by 48% utilizing a remote system and variable drain on the subjects. At lowest level the drain only transfers 5% of the subject's power to the recipient, and can be sustained for several weeks before the subject is killed. Recovery time of the subjects is currently 20 times the activation duration and is currently unsuitable for mass usage. At highest drain the subject transfers 50% of their power to the recipient, but this can only be sustained for a few minutes before the subject is killed.<br><br>Death of a subject during drain will cause a catastrophic feedback loop through the recipient and the Bloodpool system.<br><br>Recent advances have neutralized the feedback from affecting the recipient in case of subject death, but system failure is still a problem."
// Answer Text :
"P31669646" "How many subjects are there, and what is their status?"
// Page InformationPage4 Text :
"P1124600945" "There are currently 4 living subjects in the facility stasis tubes.<br><br>Subject 1: Critical Condition. Life Signs: Weak<br>Subject 2: Critical Condition. Life Signs: Moderate<br>Subject 3: Serious Condition. Life Signs: Moderate<br>Subject 4: Critical Condition. Life Signs: Weak"
// Answer Text :
"P1364819544" "Is the Bloodpool system currently engaged?"
// Page InformationPage5 Text :
"P1854751150" "Archon Dimitri is currently using the Bloodpool system."
// Answer Text :
"P1058995255" "The time to strike is now... Where is life support control?"
// Page InformationPage6 Text :
"P3964525165" "Each stasis tube has a life support computer located in this structure."<br><br><color orange>The terminal shows you the location of the life support control terminals, but as it does so a warning initiates.</color><br><br>"System Lock Out initiatied. Terminal has been compromised. Self destruct initiated."
// Answer Text :
"P2303280053" "Get to the life support control terminals"
// Page TerminalSelfDestruct Text :
"P4227491185" "3... 2... 1..."
// Answer Text :
"P1517400020" "Leave"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - VillainDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1012819405" "I... I don't understand. I am vampyri... How could you have beaten me? I had more than enough power... to destroy <i>you</i>!"
// Answer Text :
"P1049906986" "This isn't an experiment, Dimitri, there are variables you didn't consider."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1335794975" "Heh... I was wrong... about a great many things... it seems. I am most... surprised... at how wrong I was... about you.<br><br>I never anticipated that you... would take the path... of least resistance. You didn't even look for an alternative to sacrificing your comrades. So blinded by your pursuit of me... you used them... no... you murdered them, just to weaken me."
// Answer Text :
"P1007699435" "You murdered them, I did what had to be done to stop you."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P3914045522" "To stop me? Oh... There were other ways. You just chose... not to see them. You did the simpler equation... to come to the conclusion... that <i>you</i> wanted so that the hard decision... was easier. Well bravo... you got me, but at such expense... your allies are dead, and I am beaten... such a waste just to capture me."
// Answer Text :
"P715889286" "Capture? No, you're going to die for your crimes."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P1091146378" ""Of course... how could I... expect mercy... from a {hero.gender=male man|woman}... like y..."<br><br><color orange>Without a moment's hesitation, you reach down and snap Archon Dimitri's neck. He immediately slumps, his life ended.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1923204118" "There is no mercy for the merciless."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1432341247" "With the location of Archon Dimitri's base and the password for his internal security you have everything you need to infiltrate the Council facility, learn the secret to the Archon's new technology, and hopefully find a way to stop it or turn it against him. You have a feeling that Archon Dimitri's kidnapping of heroes lately has something to do with this and you aim to put an end to his terror."
// AcceptString :
"P2673881141" "Find out the secret to Archon Dimitri's new technology and stop him by any means necessary!"
// SendOffString :
"P3525003024" "Archon Dimitri's new technology is only making him stronger by the day. Fortunately someone did some very dilligent intelligence gathering, and now you have that information at your disposal. Archon Dimitri is doomed."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2143210938" "Destroy Archon Dimitri"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1397121627" "You cannot hope to face Archon Dimitri until you learn the secret to his new technology and can figure out how to destroy it or turn it against him. The longer you wait the stronger he will become until even you cannot oppose him."
// TaskTitle :
"P1949930218" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A  Trashcan Set On Vibrate</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2888402958" "The secret to Archon Dimitri's technology is here. You can feel it in the air. Now to find it and use it against him."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P603019732" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Trashcan Set On Vibrate</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>On entering Archon Dimitri's base, you found a security terminal and used the password from the PDA to access it. The records you found indicated that the abduction of heroes were linked directly to Archon Dimitri's new technology: the technology drains the power from superpowered individuals and trasfers them to Dimitri, slowly killing the individuals in the process. You discovered that the entire system would collapse if the heroes were killed suddenly. Many of them were already on death's door, so you chose to sacrifice them in order to stop Archon Dimitri and destroy his technology. With Dimitri's power waning, but not shattered, you confronted and defeated him in a final showdown. He did not beg for his life when you took it, but did question whether you were a greater villain than himself. Preposterous!"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1316115041" "Hear Archon Dimitri's final words"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P4194155848" "You've been found!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3757323359" "Defeat Adjutant Sharpe"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P1625070419" "Archon Dimitri crumples to the ground, awaiting your finishing blow."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1256279107" "Speak to Archon Dimitri"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1551075058" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>So, {HeroName}, you've learned the secret to my growing power. The only question that remains, is what do you plan to do about it?<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>I'm sure you've figured out by now that you have no hope against me so long as your comrades continue to feed me their power.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Whatever shall you do about that? I guess we shall both find out. But decide quickly. I am coming for you soon enough."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3968515777" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Amazing! You actually did it. I didn't think you had such a merciless disregard for the well being of your fellow heroes.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>But contingencies what they are, I am prepared for this. You would make a fine addition to the Council, {HeroName}, but instead I'm going to use you as the new source of my power!<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Even without my full power I can still crush you, just as I did the others."
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1499393604" "Security Terminal"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P3352135661" "This computer is connected to the nerve center of Archon Dimitri's base."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P3339495171" "Security authorization accepted."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3367926832" "Access security terminal"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3863605045" "You have uncovered the dreadful secret of Archon Dimitri's power!"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2784053200" "Adjutant Sharpe"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1207947993" "<shout>Your little intrusion ends here, {HeroName}!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2566896288" "We've heard everything."
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3307613097" "Willing to sacrifice your friends just to kill Archon Dimitri? That's very ignoble of you."
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2676967148" "What would drive a {hero.gender=male man|woman} to do such a thing?"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P896065276" "Think about what you're doing. Who's the real villain here?"
// Script Variable BOSS_DEAD_DIALOG :
"P2285853303" "Heh... you don't even see it... you're... just... like... us."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptDefeatedAmbusher 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable OBJECT_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3198780684" "Life Support Control"
// Script Variable ACTOR_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P628035877" "...but, if {HeroName} destroys these..."
// Script Variable ACTOR2_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P3656184757" "<em t=2>{hero.gender=male His|Her} friends die. Brilliant, huh?"
// Script Variable ACTOR_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P3889655098" "I don't think {hero.gender=male he|she} cares."

