"P3891858503" "Destroy the last life support control"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P891579794" "You have destroyed one of the life support systems in Archon Dimitri's base."
// Script Variable ACTOR_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P3144261658" "Remember, we can't let these modules be destroyed."
// Script Variable ACTOR2_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P3661793115" "<em t=2>Understood."
// Script Variable ACTOR_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P556344669" "Stop {hero.gender=male him|her}!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptDestroyLifeSupport 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable ACTOR_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P4049929728" "Would {HeroName} actually destroy these?"
// Script Variable ACTOR2_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P350795798" "<em t=2>I doubt it, doing so would kill {hero.gender=male his|her} comrades."
// Script Variable ACTOR_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P3120285545" "{HeroName}... this is where you die."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptDestroyLifeSupport 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable ACTOR_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P1812448364" "I heard {HeroName} is in the base."
// Script Variable ACTOR2_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P1912032079" "<em t=2>Don't worry, Archon Dimitri will deal with {hero.gender=male him|her}."
// Script Variable ACTOR_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1127904596" "There's {HeroName}, stop {hero.gender=male him|her}!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptDestroyLifeSupport 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1450667176" "Archon Dimitri"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P666145583" "Archon Dimitri has discovered a method to steal the powers from captured super heroes and graft them to himself. This has made him one of the most dangerous Archons in the Council."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P2208835517" "<shout>Like a fly to honey, {HeroName}. Only now do you realize that you have fallen into my trap!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2117289457" "Take {HeroName} alive, I have plans for {Hero.gender=male him|her}!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P4143934101" "You are full of surprises, {HeroName}. I thought for sure you would have agonized over how to save your fellow heroes.."
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P596418884" "But you don't have time for the weak, do you? Even though you could have saved them, stopping me was more important. They could have lived, all of them, but it was you who killed them."
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1651703986" "It is a shame that their sacrifice will amount to nothing. Let me show you... Augh! No... What's happening!?"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P4284120666" "You... are truly... one... of us..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptVillainConfronted 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P962480931" "Defeat Archon Dimitri"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3829169529" "You destroyed Archon Dimitri's power siphoning technology and put an end to the hero abductions, but not without great cost."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P1598946899" "{HeroName} stopped Archon Dimitri's crazy scheme to steal power from heroes and villains, but did {Hero.gender=male he|she} have to let all those people die?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL4-5_Task_04 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - AgentDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3298625617" "How the hell did you find out about this? Who's the mole?"
// Answer Text :
"P997305033" "What's the Family need with a guy like you?"
// Page Page1 Text :
"P759113387" ""Justin T. Calloway, Lieutenant, ID Number 226579."<br><br><color orange>Calloway stares blankly forward, seemingly unwilling to answer any further questions.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3436157861" "Break his arm"
// Page Page2 Text :
"P1571487151" "<color orange>Calloway screams.<br><br>Ga...gaaaaaah! Ahhh, you broke my arm... You sick piece of...""
// Answer Text :
"P2862280831" "Give him a stern look"
// Page AgentPlans Text :
"P196678814" "Gahh... Alright, fine. I'll tell you. Tommy 'Guns' Beluchi hired me on to help them do a bank job. The porter technology I have could let me bounce into a vault undetected, steal everything, and bounce out."
// Answer Text :
"P3153389247" "Beluchi? The gun smuggler? Why work with Beluchi at all?"
// Page AgentPlans2 Text :
"P2029193915" "They know things, mainly which accounts are used for government slush funds and by high ranking government officials. We hit them hard in the pocket books and we get what we want, Beluchi gets his share of the cash."
// Answer Text :
"P4163040578" "How will Beluchi know you're who you say you are?"
// Page AgentIdentification Text :
"P1459425502" "I give him a passphrase; Lead is the world's new gold."
// Answer Text :
"P4284746633" ""Great. That's all I needed to know." (Kill him)"
// Page AgentDeath Text :
"P597367954" ""What? But... I told you what you..."<br><br><color orange>Without a moment to lose you snap Calloway's spinal cord and drag him behind some boxes. You strip him of his uniform and equipment and don it yourself to complete your infiltration.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P990173096" "Continue your mission."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3080897117" "{hero.gender=male I expected something... I dunno... different|I didn't think they had dame jarheads. A pleasure to meet you}. Now you mind tellin' me A - why you are early, and B - and this is really the more important of the two questions, what the password is so I don't have to shoot you in the face?"
// Answer Text :
"P2529335705" "Lead is the world's new gold"
// Page PasswordPage Text :
"P3125354655" "Well, see, the password is correct... But you didn't tell me why you are early."
// Answer Text :
"P2343377678" "Start to make something up"
// Page FoundOutPage Text :
"P2021389588" "Don't bother... You think we don't have security cameras here in the twenty first century? What, you think we're in the 1930's cause we dress this way? I watched you kill Calloway, ditch his body behind those crates, {hero.gender=male and play dress up with his uniform, some fine work, I must say, but now I gotta kill ya|and watch you play dress up, and I must say... I liked what I saw of you, that's for sure... it is <i>really</i> too bad that I gotta kill ya}."
// Answer Text :
"P2188304684" "We'll see who kills who..."
// Page FoundOutPage2 Text :
"P3108653731" "Die you scum sucking hero!"
// Answer Text :
"P3318293876" "(Fight)"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecurityTerminalDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3121604944" "<color orange>You access the phone on Beluchi's desk looking for security system controls.</color><br><br>"Welcome to the Wareco Phone System. Please enter your PIN number now.""
// Answer Text :
"P1704737810" "Enter 4 random numbers"
// Answer Text :
"P1031216144" "(Enter the number retrieved from Beluchi)"
// Page AccessDenied Text :
"P859019744" "I'm sorry, but that PIN number is not recognized. Access is denied."
// Answer Text :
"P2882199729" "Find Beluchi's PIN number"
// Page SecurityPage Text :
"P1983795337" "Welcome <i>Tommy Beluchi</i>. Please listen to the automated menu and select your options with the number pad.<br><br>For technical assistance, please press 1.<br><br>For security system options, please press 2.<br><br>For..."
// Answer Text :
"P3689926247" "Press 2"
// Page BaseIsUnderAttack Text :
"P1970598328" "Welcome to security system options. Please listen to the automated menu and select your options with the number pad.<br><br>To activate the alarm in event of an emergency or alarm failure, please press 1.<br><br>To..."
// Answer Text :
"P4222894396" "Press 1, sound the alarm"
// Page SecurityProtocol Text :
"P3761641734" "Alarm will be sounded."
// Answer Text :
"P2608336347" "Get on the warehouse loud speaker"
// Page DestroyBase Text :
"P1126160140" "<color orange>You get on the warehouse loudspeaker and make your best impression of one of Tommy 'Guns' Beluchi's thugs.</color><br><br><i>Everybody... dem jarheads double crossed us and done whacked Tommy, everybody get out, this place is gonna be crawlin' with coppers any minute.</i>""
// Answer Text :
"P1363710961" "You think they bought it"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2401757473" "Lieutenant Calloway is not the type of man to act without approval from his superiors. If he were to wind up dead on an operation with the Family involved, then that could spark a little war between the Family and the Sky Raiders. You just have to make sure that you get your hands on Calloway before the Family does, and that means getting to the rendezvous first."
// AcceptString :
"P3484976616" "Start a little war between the Sky Raiders and the Family."
// SendOffString :
"P3561770106" "Eliminating someone like Calloway is good on its own, but the chance to turn that victory into a war between two of your enemies is even better. With any luck they'll destroy each other, or at least weaken themselves to the point that they can't stop you from finishing them off. Once Calloway has been eliminated you can assume his identity and assassinate whoever is representing the Family at this little meet and greet."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2875368195" "Start a war"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3480797552" "You'll need to eliminate Calloway before the Family sees him, then you can take his identity and meet with the Family boss responsible for this whole meeting and kill him. The Family and Sky Raiders will assume they were betrayed by the other and the bullets will start flying."
// TaskTitle :
"P733638152" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Pizza Sauce Stained Sticky Note</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P303203677" "You emerge from your hiding place in the warehouse as Calloway and his entourage show up. The Family will never know what hit them!"
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2184694411" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Pizza Sauce Stained Sticky Note</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Not bad for a day's work. You eliminated one of the Sky Raider's elite specialists, shut down a major Family operation, and started a war between the Sky Raiders and the Family. You're pretty sure that there will be some collateral damage when the Sky Raiders start shooting, but that matters little. With any luck the Sky Raiders will take a big chunk out of the Family, or they'll bite off more than they can chew and lose a lot of irreplaceable men. Either way, in the long run, the good guys win this one!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P76640799" "Lieutenant Calloway collapses to the ground, speak to him."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P179191711" "Talk to Calloway"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P1403548720" "You have claimed the identity of Lieutenant Calloway! The Family will not attack you, believing you are their contact."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1993214467" "Lieutenant Calloway's Identity Assumed!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P1864909331" "The warehouse has been alerted to your farce! The Family will attack you on sight!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P34089015" "Identity Compromised"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1907149444" "Speak to Tommy 'Guns' Beluchi"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2606144747" "Lieutenant Calloway"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P1898001453" "Lieutenant Calloway is an operations officer that works directly under Colonel Duray, and is the head of special operations for a unit of Porter equipped soldiers in the Sky Raiders tasked with cleaning out bank vaults by porting directly into them, bypassing conventional security."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1676442873" "This is the place. It's unlike Beluchi to not have a pair of fat thugs guarding the door. They must be keeping a low profile for this op."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P610212454" "{HeroName}!? It's a trap!"
// Script Variable BOSS_1STBLOOD_DIALOG :
"P2019546318" "Either Beluchi double crossed me, or you took him out and were waiting for me. Either way, this operation is over."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P3119619790" "What do you want?"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2005799751" "This isn't over, {HeroName}! Duray will have your head!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1096561021" "Ga...gaaaaaah! Ahhh, you broke my arm... you sick piece of..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptAgentHealth25 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3044835560" "Defeat Lieutenant Calloway"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1106897581" "Tommy 'Guns' Beluchi"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P3167813623" "Tommy 'Guns' Beluchi is a notorious gun runner for the Family. He is looking to expand his buying power and so began talks with the Sky Raiders in an attempt to pull off some get rich quick bank vault jobs using one of their Porters, Lieutenant Calloway."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1904795875" "<shout>No, listen Sam, I don't care... No, you find those guns and whoever stole them off your dock, and you bring them to me!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P4027007353" "Nobody likes a double crossing liar. I'm gonna drop you into the bay with fifty pounds of lead in your body to weigh you down!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3318805133" "You can't stop us, {HeroName}."
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P4100933706" "We own the judges. I'll be out inside a week. You'll see."
// Script Variable BOSS_DEAD_DIALOG :
"P3277537168" "Ugghhh."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P3640353863" "You're early? Didn't Al "

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptBossDead 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3638464779" "Defeat Tommy 'Guns' Beluchi"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1217089558" "Beluchi's Desk"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P2619354639" "This is Beluchi's desk, it is likely filled with all kinds of incriminating information and has a phone you can use to initiate the warehouse alarm."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2711295453" "Look over Beluchi's desk"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3199646020" "You killed Lieutenant Calloway, stopped Tommy 'Guns' Beluchi from becoming an even bigger supplier of guns to the criminal underworld and even managed to start a war between the Family and the Sky Raiders."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P2659085807" "Something has the Family running scared and shooting at anything that moves."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL4-5_Task_05 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BodyguardDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P715721481" "Stop! We're defecting! We're leaving our lives in Arachnos behind us. We're looking to do some good in this world now. Can't you see that? Can't you believe in that?"
// Answer Text :
"P1272353293" "I believe in good and evil, and you're evil!"
// Page Page2 Text :
"P626259432" "I was evil... But no longer. I've seen what Recluse would have me do and I want nothing to do with that madman any longer. All of us on this ship feel the same. We're through with Arachnos, through with Recluse, and through with the Rogue Isles.<br><br>Now that that is sorted out, why are you here?"
// Answer Text :
"P412647989" "You're going to help me get Westmore."
// Page StartTorture Text :
"P3056071472" "Westmore? No way... I'm not telling you a thing, he's like a brother to me. There is nothing you can say or do that will make me betray him."
// Answer Text :
"P994968235" ""I think I have my ways." (Break Green's ribs)"
// Answer Text :
"P800892077" ""I don't have time for games." (Gouge out Green's eye)"
// Answer Text :
"P1262216935" ""Oh, I think you'll talk." (Break Green's leg)"
// Answer Text :
"P3376644844" "Now then, where were we?"
// Page TortureMethod1 Text :
"P3694325106" "<color orange>You unbuckled Green's chest armor and start wailing on his ribs</color><br><br>"Ugh... Ugh... Ufff! Gah! Gaaaah.... You {hero.gender=male son of a|little}... Graaaah! Stop... My lungs... Ahhhh..."<br><br><color orange>Green coughs violently and you see blood dribble out from under his helmet, you must have hit something vital. It looks like that really hurt.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1657269127" "Are we on the same page now?"
// Page TortureMethod2 Text :
"P818855961" "<color orange>You wrench off Green's helmet and toss it aside, then dig your thumb into one of his eyes</color><br><br>"What are you... Ah! Aaaaaahhhhh! Stop-Stop-Stop!"<br><br><color>Green clutches his face, blood streaked across his fingers as he howls in pain.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1664441431" "Don't make me take the other one."
// Page TortureMethod3 Text :
"P2734315257" "<color orange>You slam your foot down directly into the side of one of Green's legs. With a sickening pop his leg buckles, but his armor keeps him upright. He screams in unholy pain.</color><br><br>"Gaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaah! You broke my leg... Gah! Ha... Ha ha... I can't believe you broke my leg... what is wrong with you!?""
// Answer Text :
"P3254838020" "This can be the beginning, or the end, your choice."
// Page BodyguardTalks Text :
"P1707804011" "Alright! Alright... What do you want from me? Just... please... Just stop."
// Answer Text :
"P2143618691" "First, shut down the alarm and radio an all clear."
// Page BodyguardAlarmOff Text :
"P308794910" "Alright, I'll radio in that the alarm was accidently set off. Is that all?"
// Answer Text :
"P2151190302" "Now, tell Fairchild to meet you in the bow cargo bay"
// Page BodyguardLovedOne Text :
"P247265831" "Fairchild? Why do you want her? Alright alright... Just... Give me a moment and I'll have her meet us up front. Anything else?"
// Answer Text :
"P1650887356" ""Good, now... What?" (Shut him up)"
// Page BodyguardDies Text :
"P2149676549" "<color orange>You stop Green's betrayal of your presence a moment too late, delivering a swift kick to the side of his head.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P784769837" ""Now I'm angry!" (Kill Green)"
// Page BodyguardEnd Text :
"P3830209024" "<color orange>Before Green can recover from the kick you grab his head and yank it hard to the side. He goes rigid for a moment and then relaxes.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P4223467109" "I should have expected that from a traitor."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - LovedOneDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3288303336" "What are you doing? I can't read you, all I see is death and anger. Please, we've seen enough of that. Let us start new lives. Have you no mercy?"
// Answer Text :
"P1126417729" ""There is no mercy for the merciless." (Twist her arm)"
// Page LovedOneTorture1 Text :
"P944582534" ""Ahhhh! Stop! Stop!!"<br><br><color orange>Fairchild goes silent for a moment and you know that she is contacting Westmore mentally. Just what you wanted.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P960645059" ""That's right, cry for help!" (Knock the wind out of her)"
// Page LovedOneTorture2 Text :
"P3530276113" "Gaaaaaaahhh..."<br><br><color orange>As she gasps for breath, you can tell that Fairchild is having a difficult time keeping in contact with her boyfriend. No man could resist coming to the aid of his imperiled woman.</color><br><br>"You'll pay for this, {HeroName}..."
// Answer Text :
"P894913900" ""You mean when Westmore shows up?" (Strike her in the temple)"
// Page LovedOneTorture3 Text :
"P1790604913" "<color orange>Fairchild staggers from your blow, you can tell she is in no condition to send a mental message. She's frightened.</color><br><br>"What? You... you wanted Westmore to show up? Oh no... what have I done? My love...!""
// Answer Text :
"P2292811905" ""We're all done here." (Kill Fairchild)"
// Page LovedOneEnd Text :
"P2322876381" "<color orange>Fairchild must have got some semblance of a message off to Westmore, because as you deliver the killing blow you hear Westmore bellow in the distance.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3590799" "Shhh, you'll be with him again soon."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BossDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3027891044" "You... I don't even know... what to call you... {HeroName}... you're as bad as Recluse! No... you're worse! Recluse makes no claim to be a force for good... you masquerade as a champion... of the people, but in the end you're the monster that will be their doom."
// Answer Text :
"P3705575600" "People like you never change, always blaming others for your misdeeds."
// Page BossText2 Text :
"P633860149" "You're wrong... people change all the time. In fact, {HeroName}, all you need to do... is look in the mirror to see... just how much you've changed... just how far you've fallen."<br><br>Heh... I remember a time... when you were the hero you pretend to be. I used to admire you... your courage, your conviction to stand up... against the odds. You're the reason... the reason I decided to defect... why Brittany and Robert... why they followed me. They saw in me... what I once saw in you..."
// Answer Text :
"P3596227322" "What quality of mine could you possibly possess?"
// Page BossText3 Text :
"P3378395500" "Hope... {HeroName}... you gave me hope, and in turn... I gave that hope to them. Now they are dead... and I soon with them. Well, get it over with. I would rather die... at the hands of a <i>hero</i>... then live in the world... that they could justify doing so."
// Answer Text :
"P986475041" ""Then I shall grant this wish." (Kill Westmore)"
// Page MissionEnd Text :
"P591420410" "<color orange>Westmore doesn't even struggle, he almost gladly gives his life, hoping that after this world he will again see his love in the next. But you know, there can be no love, no forgiveness, until one has been punished for their sins.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P373753178" "Hope is for those too weak to act."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3857735715" "Huntsman Westmore is cautious, that's the only way he's been able to keep this little mutiny off of Arachnos's radar for this long. Unfortunately that caution is going to make things a lot harder on him. The surest way to get him to show himself will be to target his girlfriend, Fortunata Fairchild. You're counting on her psychically calling for help to draw Westmore out. Unfortunately, she's got a nasty Crab Spider as a bodyguard, so you'll have to deal with him first."
// AcceptString :
"P3380473244" "Draw Westmore and his friends out to pay for their crimes."
// SendOffString :
"P2647309267" "Every member of Arachnos is guilty of innumerable crimes. That fact alone justifies everything you are about to do here today. You'll need to eliminate Fairchild's bodyguard, then draw her into the trap. Her cries of pain will draw Westmore to you like a spider to a fly, only you're a bug killer."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2977432397" "Lure Westmore into your trap"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1396886998" "Westmore isn't aboard the ship, you're going to have to use his girlfriend to draw him back and into a proper showdown to pay for his crimes. You're going to enjoy this."
// TaskTitle :
"P3533704886" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Squawk From An Arachnos Headset</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P4253688695" "You've watched the ships for a few hours and decided to trip a door alarm on the vessel in order to draw out Fairchild's Crab Spider bodyguard, Robert Green."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3787114737" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Squawk From An Arachnos Headset</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You think about what Westmore said to you before you ended him. You're nothing like Recluse. Recluse is a brutal Tyrant who kills for his own ends. You are a merciless agent of vengeance who punishes the wicked. That Westmore saw the evil in Recluse and was horrified is commendable, but it does nothing to redeem him for the numerous crimes he performed in the name of Arachnos. There is only one true path to redemption; death, and you are the ferryman come to collect the toll."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3253222815" "Speak to Robert Green before finishing him"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3533791710" "Find Fairchild and capture her"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3403044716" "Speak to Fairchild before finishing her"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2737170599" "Find Westmore and defeat him"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P636253586" "Speak to Westmore before finishing him"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2127319713" "Robert Green collapses to the ground. Make him call for Fairchild"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1311188126" "Talk to Robert Green"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2677928588" "Fairchild collapses to the ground. Make her scream to draw out Westmore."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3500457692" "Make Fairchild scream for help"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P4129690080" "Westmore collapses before you. Give him his last rites."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P379658925" "Talk to Westmore"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3921615653" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>This is Green. False alarm. Go ahead and shut it off."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P659257339" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Fairchild, this is Green. I'm going to need you to... Go to full alert, {HeroName} is here!"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P898669013" "Robert Green"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P2162641174" "Robert Green was once just another faceless Crab Spider thug in the service of Arachnos. Then one day he was asked to go too far, to kill too much, and he snapped. Brittany Fairchild sensed his growing rebellion against Arachnos and together they have worked to find more people like them who want to get out and make a new life. Robert has served as Brittany's bodyguard ever since they met."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3113573788" "<shout>We've got an alarm on the cargo door. I'll handle it."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P3723828205" "{HeroName}?!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P924506110" "You don't understand, we're defecting!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3754120385" "Man, they weren't kidding, you are tough!"
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P317004070" "Alright, I give!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptBodyguardDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P1030740843" "Eliminate Robert Green"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P4255386617" "Brittany Fairchild"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P1789730778" "Once a Fortunata Seer working for Arachnos, Brittany Fairchild had seen enough and wanted out. She began searching for others like her and found Alan Westmore. Together they have rallied together others who wish to leave Arachnos and make a new life for themselves in the United States, beyond Lord Recluse's reach."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P513980516" "<shout>Everyone on high alert. Green's down, {HeroName} is here! Don't let {hero.gender=male him|her} get through!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1793190343" "You killed Green, {HeroName}. Don't you get it? We aren't with Arachnos anymore!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2046830165" "If it's a fight you want, then you'll get one!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2795765727" "Enough... Please!"
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P2105001660" "Believe me, {HeroName}, we aren't with Arachnos anymore."

