"P374932513" "You have delt with Westmore."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P913278895" "Sure, {HeroName} eliminated Alan Westmore, but are heroes supposed to go to such extreme measures?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL4-5_Task_06 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - FoughtFirstHeroBoss 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P130149655" "Field Commander Shattuck"
// DetailString :
"P2186731798" "You and Field Commander Shattuck could not come to an agreement concerning Captain Anderson's traitorous actions. You resorted to killing him so that you could pin the murder on Anderson in order to convince Overdrive that Anderson was a traitor."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - FirstHeroBossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2662932533" "{HeroName}. I didn't know you were being sent as backup. I could really use someone of your calibre."
// Answer Text :
"P747445383" "I'm not backup, I'm a rescue team. Where's Anderson?"
// Page WorkingWithVillain Text :
"P237107983" "Anderson is leading a team in through the east wing. I have to say, I wasn't sure of him at first, but he has supplied us with priceless information about the Sky Raiders. This entire operation was his brain child."
// Answer Text :
"P4257303137" "This entire operation was a set up. Anderson played you."
// Page IHaveProof Text :
"P4260624240" "That's some pretty stiff accusations there, {HeroName}, do you have proof?"<br><br><color orange>You show the commander the pictures you took of Anderson outside the club, and then play him the message that Sabre left you, explaining that Sabre is a contact you have in the Federal Bureau.</color><br><br>This is inconclusive. Even if everything these photos and this <i>Sabre</i> say is true, it in no way proves that Anderson is betraying us. Sabre said that Santiago and Weller were missing since after the Rikti War. For all we know they were never a part of the Sky Raiders to begin with. Maybe he was just catching up on old times. The bottom line is, you are jumping to conclusions that prove what you want to be true. You're going to need more concerete evidence of Anderson's betrayal than this before I call this operation off. Do you have anything that <i>proves</i> he is betraying us, or just wild speculation?"
// Answer Text :
"P2223703688" "I do... your dead body."
// Page BetrayFirstHeroBoss Text :
"P2941821682" "What? What are you talking about?"
// Answer Text :
"P1634211815" "I blame your death on Anderson and your team lives."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecondHeroBossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2157153353" "{HeroName}? Thank goodness you're here. This mission is totally sideways."
// Answer Text :
"P314272194" "Of course it is, Anderson's betrayed you."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1520232549" "What?! But, he's been working with Longbow for months, he helped stop a dozen or more Sky Raider heists in that time. Commander Shattuck trusts him, and that's good enough for me."
// Answer Text :
"P458546324" "Shattuck's dead, Anderson killed him."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P4983270" "<color orange>Overdrive gives you a shocked look and then radios for Commander Shattuck.</color orange><br><br>"Commander Shattuck, this is Overdrive, please respond. Commander Shattuck, do you read? Damn...<br><br>Dead... {HeroName}, what are we going to do? If Anderson has been double crossing us the whole time, then we've walked right into a trap!""
// Answer Text :
"P1285906606" "Anderson doesn't know I'm here, we'll take him out together!"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P1892188789" "Burned out a power core or not, I've still got enough juice left in my armor to show Anderson a thing or two!"
// Answer Text :
"P4124785633" "Let's do this."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1358747459" "For the past few weeks, Captain Anderson has been hard at work <i>redeeming</i> himself, even teaming up with Longbow to take his old unit down. It all seemed a bit too good to be true, given his past in the Sky Raiders, so you started doing surveillance on him. You snapped a few pictures of Anderson meeting some people outside of a night club a few days ago. You sent copies of the photos to Sabre, your contact in the Feds, and after a few days received confirmation of your suspicions. Anderson is meeting his old Sky Raider buddies incognito. He's acting as a double agent!"
// AcceptString :
"P2949995387" "Prove Captain Anderson's guilt to Longbow."
// SendOffString :
"P1219355014" "Longbow is currently underway on an offensive operation to take down some of the Sky Raiders, using Anderson's intel. It's obviously a trap. You need to get in touch with the Longbow Field Commander and warn him of Anderson's treachery. If that doesn't work, then you'll have to use extreme measures to convince Longbow that Anderson can't be trusted."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P4093404829" "Prove Captain Anderson's guilt"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P880393609" "Find the Longbow Field Commander and show him the evidence you have against Anderson. If he refuses to pull his men back then you will just have to kill the commander and blame it on Anderson. At least the other Longbow agents will survive, despite their commander's ignorance. You hope it doesn't come to that."
// TaskTitle :
"P2569806466" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Your Friend, Sabre, Called</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2869904313" "You listen to the orders being issued over the Longbow operational channel. It looks like the operation has already begun. You can only hope they will listen to you."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1874406411" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Your Friend, Sabre, Called</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Captain Anderson's lies and deceit were finally exposed by your diligent efforts. It is unfortunate that Longbow had to lose one of their Field Commanders before Anderson's betrayal was believed, but the ends justify the means. Better for one soldier to die than his entire squad."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2236399586" "You've rescued the Field Commander. Speak to him about Anderson."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3830994626" "Speak to the Field Commander"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P716016174" "Defeat the Field Commander"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P3869630726" "You have rescued Overdrive. Talk to her about Captain Anderson."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1559067150" "Speak to Overdrive!"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3362990853" "Speak to Overdrive"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P740302928" "Withstand the Sky Raider counter attack!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2289893609" "The Sky Raiders are sending an assault force to your position!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3621492681" "Enemy forces approaching!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1281987799" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Overdrive, this is Field Commander Shattuck. I have neutralized the security system, you should be clear to breach the ventillation system now. Over.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>Overdrive here, I'm starting my entry. I'm going radio silent and will contact you within five minutes. Over.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Copy that, Overdrive. Shattuck out.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Wait... I've got someone coming... is anyone in sector 1? Uh oh. I'm in trouble here! Anyone, please respond. This is Commander Shattuck in sector 1, I need backup! I need..."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3905723223" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>This is Overdrive. Commander Shattuck, I have breached the interior but need help. I've located a sizeable Sky Raider force and need immediate assistance... Commander, do you read?"
// Script Variable PET_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3621650440" "Bring it,you gutless cowards!"
// Script Variable SayOnRescue :
"P1871829278" "Great timing, {HeroName}."
// Script Variable RescueObjectiveText :
"P1003273166" "Find the Field Commander"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1960966216" "Lieutenant Weller"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1210817641" "Don't kill him yet... I want to enjoy this."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2369338688" "What?! {HeroName}!? Get {hero.gender=male him|her}!"
// Script Variable SayOnBetrayal :
"P4165993914" "You're insane! Overdrive will never believe you!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptFirstHeroBossRescued 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable PET_NAME :
"P1900839643" "Overdrive"
// Script Variable PET_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3229161134" "<em t=3>Really? Show me how training stops this!"
// Script Variable PET_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3879404405" "Reinforcements. You guys are going to--what's happening?!<em>Ugh, armor...shorting out again."
// Script Variable SayOnRescue :
"P4027447832" "{HeroName}! You're a welcome relief. Where's the Field Commander?"
// Script Variable RescueObjectiveText :
"P726188482" "Find Overdrive"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2591922995" "Sergeant Santiago"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3139837459" "Power armor is no match for training and experience."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P776709233" "We've got company!"
// Script Variable CAPTOR_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P4251617798" "<em t=3>Stop toying with her, Santiago, and help me finish her off."
// Script Variable CAPTOR_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3159648487" "Open fire!"
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P3036648432" "Let's figure out what our next plan of action is."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P4099178074" "I'm okay now, let's get moving."

