// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL4-5_Task_08 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - AllyConflictDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2958813993" "My strength's returning, now I can convince Nocturne to indoctrinate me into Arachnos so I can have my vengeance against the Freedom Phalanx!<br><br>Thanks, {HeroName}, I couldn't have done this without you."
// Answer Text :
"P2936278911" "'What? You're joining Arachnos!?"
// Page VillainToPrison Text :
"P162869214" "Why else would I be after Nocturne? She's a powerful agent in Arachnos. I'm sure she'll gladly welcome me into their organization in exchange for me sparing her life."
// Answer Text :
"P3197230861" "You're not going to kill her!?"
// Page VillainToPrison2 Text :
"P4015134742" "Of course not! She's visiting suffering on those miserable heroes of the Freedom Phalanx. She and I have the same goals. Now that you've proven how capable we are they'd be fools not to welcome us into their ranks. Think of it, {HeroName}, with Arachnos troops under our command we can make those responsible for pain and suffering in this world pay for their crimes! Now help Nocturne up and let's get out of here."
// Answer Text :
"P1738161950" "Arachnos is responsible for pain and suffering across the Rogue Isles."
// Page VillainToPrison3 Text :
"P645787271" "I thought you would see eye to eye with me on this, {HeroName}. Arachnos may be filled with cold hearted killers, but how is that any different than what you or I do to evil doers? The key is to direct the pain and suffering against people who deserve it, like Positron and his stupid Freedom Phalanx! Or the coward who killed my parents!"
// Answer Text :
"P2676000885" "I can't let you do this, Arachnos is evil... and so are you."
// Page VillainToPrison4 Text :
"P4224119866" "Fine! I appreciate your help, but if you won't join me, then I don't need you!"
// Answer Text :
"P1148704378" "Fine!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2433419636" "Savage Siren is a dangerous vigilante who does whatever it takes to deliver justice to evil doers. It sounds like she's cornered Nocturne along with a cadre of her Freakshow friends down in the sewers, so you're on your way to give her a hand. Nocturne is a monster who must pay for her crimes!"
// AcceptString :
"P4025823005" "With you and Savage Siren on Nocturne's trail, there's no escape for her!"
// SendOffString :
"P3742456329" "You're actually sort of excited. Savage Siren doesn't mess around, and she's made it no secret that she can't stand the law abiding 'heroes' of Paragon City. You have a feeling that the two of you are going to work together just fine."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3650475999" "Help Savage Siren deliver swift justice"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P21094793" "Your first order of business is going to be finding Savage Siren. The two of you working together should be able to stop anything Nocturne and those cybernetic Freaks can throw at you. After that, it'll come down to drawing straws to see who gets to deliver justice."
// TaskTitle :
"P1002123913" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Siren's Call</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1367838459" "Nocturne's back is against the wall, today she and those Freaks pay for their crimes!"
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P4236136808" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Siren's Call</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You should have known that Savage Siren's personal issues were going to get in the way of justice. Her vendetta against the hero that killed her family is one thing, but she's lost sight of who her enemy really is. Trying to join Arachnos to get back at Heroes in general? Ridiculous. Nocturne got away, but at least you taught Savage Siren a lesson. Maybe when she regains consciousness she'll realize that she messed up trying to join the other team. Especially when Nocturne comes looking for her revenge."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P1466095272" "Savage Siren wants to talk to you."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P2042332805" "Talk to Savage Siren"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3354851518" "Defeat Night Widow Nocturne"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1530353613" "Defeat Savage Siren"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_NAME :
"P34356174" "Savage Siren"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P2594747832" "<shout>You Freaks aren't gonna stop me!"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P168547518" "{HeroName}! I was starting to wonder if you were gonna show."
// Script Variable SayOnRescue :
"P3846612701" "Let's hash out a plan."
// Script Variable SayOnRecapture :
"P4060030436" "<shout>Listen, let's talk about this."
// Script Variable SayOnRerescue :
"P4186241546" "Thanks for the help."
// Script Variable SayOnStranded :
"P958960967" "<shout>Where did you go?"
// Script Variable CAPTOR_NAME :
"P1371141630" "PUNk Shocker"
// Script Variable CAPTOR_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3270177420" "<shout><em t=3>Ehahaha! You're not pretty, you're electro-cute! Ahaha ha!"
// Script Variable CAPTOR_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P2080523510" "Shocker, I hardly knew her! Ah ha ha ha!"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3251547047" "Meat Doctor"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P996935787" "<shout><em t=6>Enough with the puns!<em>Shock her and knock her out already!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2459136233" "<em t=3>Stop. With. The. Puns. And get {HeroName}!"
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P1972422568" "Wait, don't finish her."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3937416022" "{HeroName}, they took a lot out of me, but there's no time to rest! We have to hurry, Nocturne is going to get away!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P322174963" "Wait! Stop! I need her alive."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P499716256" "FINE!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptHeroAllyRescued 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3452074932" "Find Savage Siren"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1590788888" "Night Widow Nocturne"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P2777142269" "<shout>I don't care if someone is here. Eliminate them to show Lord Recluse you are worthy of his patronage."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1006452885" "Can't you idiots eliminate a pair of mewling heroes? Kill them!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2990786270" "Funny, I was already planning on killing you, {HeroName}."
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P176837911" "Once I've finished with your {hero.gender=male boyfriend|little friend}, I'm killing you, Savage Siren."
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3332877946" "Enough! I surrender."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3868578371" "Idiots..."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1291630384" "Ha ha ha! Thanks for giving me time to escape, heroes!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptVillainDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P4241414299" "You stopped Savage Siren from joining Arachnos, but Night Widow Nocturne got away while you were fighting. At least you haven't let your quest for vengeance turn you into a monster. You can only hope that Savage Siren sees the error of her ways, or next time, you'll have to kill her."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P1119552952" "I saw Savage Siren crawl out of a sewer last night. She looked like she'd gotten run over by a truck."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL4-5_Task_09 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - ConsortiumSecurityAccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2911847574" "The Chief of Security's Passcard"
// DetailString :
"P2048085851" "This simple plastic card contains a tiny chip that should enable you to access the editing room's computer system without any problems."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - ConsortiumTruckKey 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P3664375546" "Keys to the Security Van"
// DetailString :
"P3219319108" "These are the keys to the security van and your ticket out of the building without getting stopped by security."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecurityTerminalDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1963079463" "Welcome to the EditMax Pro Platinum Video and Audio Editing computer system. How would you like to proceed?"
// Answer Text :
"P770029706" "Tamper with the items for the pledge drive"
// Answer Text :
"P2817572682" "Send an e-mail"
// Answer Text :
"P4149675579" "Search for alternative exits"
// Page NoAccess Text :
"P1210084336" "I'm sorry, you have not yet inserted your securpass passcard. Please see the chief of security currently on staff to proceed."
// Answer Text :
"P841842995" "Find the Chief of Security (Leave)"
// Page TamperWithMaterials Text :
"P2089045198" ""Request confirmed."<br><br><color orange>You splice together a few segments of unedited material, adjust teleprompter information to point out some juicy secrets that the Cage Consortium has been hiding from the international community, and even throw in some footage of a miner demonstration that was brutally put down by Consortium Guards a few weeks ago for good measure. As a final act you plant evidence of a plot to funnel the charity money into an off shore bank account and then report the funds stolen by the Sky Raiders.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1622178282" "Access Security Footage and Computer Logs"
// Page AccessSecurityFootage Text :
"P955317376" ""Security footage accessed."<br><br><color orange>You edit the security footage, making it appear that nothing unusual has happened this evening.<br><br>You edit the computer logs so that your time in the system was unrecorded, you also adjusted the creation date of the document overviewing the Sky Raider plot and then delete it, leaving it in the deleted files folder, but it is still recoverable.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2293598396" "Send an e-mail to the media"
// Page NotifyTheMedia Text :
"P2367701733" "<color orange>You draft an e-mail containing a copy of the Sky Raider plot and send it with a 12 hour delay. The e-mail won't be sent until well after the charity event and pledge drive has begun.<br><br>Just as you are finishing up the computer locks you out indicating a security breach within the office has been detected.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3392050930" "Search for alternate exits"
// Page UnlockRearDoors Text :
"P2011769819" "<color orange>You access the various security cameras around the building and notice that camera 4 is watching a back door near the building's loading docks. There is a security van that appears to have arrived in response to the silent alarm and the Consortium Security team is entering the building. You can easily avoid the security team and get to the loading dock and escape using their own security van. Unfortunately, you're going to need the keys, but fortunately the van's driver is waiting by the back entrance.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P859534160" "Deactivate camera 4 and get those keys!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3363415742" "You did a little question and answer with some people on the streets and learned that the Cage Consortium is planning their little 'charity event' in a nice cushy office building. You know that Kirk Cage would rather sell his own kid than lose money he didn't have to, so there's something awfully fishy about this whole charity, and it isn't just to improve his public image. You are almost certain that he's found a way to use the oppression of his workers as a means to drum up funding via fake charity events. He'll probably just improve working conditions for a few months and then blame the return of poor conditions on the Freakshow and a budget increase for his private security force.<br><br>Well no more, you're going to expose just how vile the Cage Consortium really is by tampering with their charity drive's telethon prompts and messages to the public. With any luck, Cage will turn their own horrid business practice into an international human rights violation, and you're guessing that Lord Recluse won't find that too amusing!"
// AcceptString :
"P253500417" "If the world can't see that the Cage Consortium is evil, then I'll make them see it!"
// SendOffString :
"P1275383457" "It's not going to be easy, what with Cage's private security force, but they're not used to dealing with people of your capability. Your first task will be to get access to the editing room computer, and that means taking out the head of security to steal his passcard."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2807688635" "Sabotage Cage Consortium's world credibility"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P4147011118" "You'll need to get in, find a security passcard, and then access their video editing equipment. Once you have access to the computer system you can edit the charity event tapes and information, plant some evidence, and erase any trace of you being in the building. It should be a piece of cake!"
// TaskTitle :
"P1796535372" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Broken Protest Sign</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3579767487" "This office is fairly quiet. If the protestors knew about it you're sure security would have been tighter. In this case you're glad that the Cage Consortium can keep a secret or two."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P154005752" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Broken Protest Sign</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>That didn't go smoothly, but it went well. If the Cage Consortium doesn't look too closely then their charity drive celebrities will reveal embarrassing secrets about the Cage Consortium's illegal practices. Even if they do catch it in time, your message to the press will cause a radical stir and the finger pointing will begin. Someone will crack and potentially go to the international community with evidence in order to save their own butt, and the whole thing will turn into a nightmare as the world stage hosts a humanitarian crisis in the Rogue Isles. Kirk Cage will be fighting that political battle for some time, and Lord Recluse is going to have to put the hurt on some bad people for you if he wants to make sure that the Rogue Isles still has a seat in the United Nations. Justice has been served."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P3583039591" "The Security Van Driver uses a combat stimulant and recovers some health!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1393165708" "The Security Van Driver regenerates!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2569247122" "The Security Van Driver has called in Reinforcements!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P2965404695" "Reinforcements Incoming!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P1497897487" "The Security Van Driver's combat stimulants have kicked in and he regenerates!"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P270288486" "Access the Editing Computer"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1038222854" "Chief of Security"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P2879382752" "<shout>Alright, I'm checking out the front door now. Keep your eyes on the monitors and not the TV, numb skulls."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptFirstBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2199428237" "Defeat the Chief of Security""

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P4130218143" "You've acquired the passcard needed to access the editing room computer."
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2661577601" "Editing Computer"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P984330806" "This computer is a hightech piece of editing equipment. With it you can take hundreds of samples and easily splice them together in order to completely modify the Consortium's pledge drive teleprompters and Public Messages campaign."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P2204599434" "Welcome"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1401149038" "Security Van Driver"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1568930269" "<shout>No, it's real quiet down here. I'll alert you if anything happens that we can't handle."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P405491381" "Who are you?"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P733830331" "Good thing I've got these combat stims!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P19867515" "This is door guard, we've got a dang hero down here! Get your butts back here!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P4200712425" "Oh man, these combat stims are kickin' in!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecondBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P1264170348" "Defeat the Security Van Driver"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P2176088278" "You have acquired the keys to the security van. Now you can make your escape and deny the security team pursuit. You're sure you can find a few protestors who wouldn't mind trashing Consortium property and taking care of the evidence for you."
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P1601165103" "<shout>Dang it! They got around behind us somehow. Let's move!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P142950313" "What the heck is {hero.gender=male he|she} doing here!?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3542308902" "You didn't find any actual evidence that the Cage Consortium was going to steal the funds for their charity drive, but that doesn't matter. They're guilty of so many other crimes, nobody will bat an eye at one little made up crime. The lid is off and now the world is going to come down hard on the Cage Consortium. But not nearly as hard as Lord Recluse will.<br><br>You ditched the van, and the unconscious Consortium security team you threw into the back, next to a group of disgruntled looking Scrapyarders and told them to have a blast. The mushroom cloud as you walked away tells you that that's exactly what they did."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P516343792" "I heard the Cage Consortium charity drive was actually a plot by the company to steal the money and line their pockets with it. Some news reporter for channel 8 broke the story."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL4-5_Task_10 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - HeroDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1736086214" "{HeroName}! What are you doing? Shouldn't we be stopping The Lost?"
// Answer Text :
"P1719301048" "I'm doing what needs to be done. You're too soft on villains."
// Answer Text :
"P2794759689" "You treat villains like they have rights. They don't."
// Answer Text :
"P3909229121" "I'm teaching you a valuable lesson, Kuwalski. Stay alive."
// Page TooLenient Text :
"P136330839" ""Too soft? Why, I'll have you know that I've never allowed a suspect to escape justice! Every one of the people I've apprehended has gone to the Zig and stood trial."<br><br><color orange>It's sickening, he's actually proud of his boy scout record.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3194765385" "The law doesn't work. We are justice and there is no room for mercy."
// Page TooLenient2 Text :
"P3374503877" "What do you mean 'no room for mercy'?"<br><br><color orange>He actually did it, he did the hand quotes. That just pisses you off.</color><br><br>"Are you saying I should just kill these people? That's what they are, {HeroName}, people, like you and I. Killing them is ludicrous, it goes against everything I believe in and it would make me no better than them!<br><br>Look, {HeroName}, I appreciate you trying to give me pointers and all, but let's just find this equipment, destroy it, and bust these perps, ok?"
// Answer Text :
"P3467735188" "I see I'll have to convince you the hard way, very well."
// Page TryingAgain Text :
"P3886922908" "We've been through this before, {HeroName}. I'm not budging on my high moral ground here. Let's just find the tech and destroy it so it can't harm anyone, ok?"
// Answer Text :
"P677133360" "Fine, but we aren't done with this conversation."
// Page TeachingALesson Text :
"P2616376704" "What lesson could you possible teach me through this.. this... treachery!? This is an atrocity, {HeroName}! You're no better than those murderers in the Zig!"
// Answer Text :
"P418394931" "Really? I did just save your hide... And I won't kill you!"
// Page TeachingALesson2 Text :
"P4145665474" "<color orange>As you deactivate the mind probe and release Kuwalski, his voice grows stronger.</color><br><br>I... I realize that this is what The Lost would have done to me if you hadn't arrived, and that I am a little headstrong, {HeroName}, but rescuing me doesn't excuse you from what you just did. You don't seem to realize that what you just did is wrong. There is no justification for these actions. The only difference between you and a villain is a difference of degree. You can't say 'I'm not as bad as them so it's ok'."<br><br><color orange>He did the hand quotes again. Rage.</color><br><br>"In the end, you did to me what they would have done just to try and prove that you are right. Well, all you proved is that I'm right. I'll never do what you do because I'm a good guy. You... I'm not so sure.""
// Answer Text :
"P3435579515" "Why not judge the villains as harshly as you do me?"
// Page TeachingALesson3 Text :
"P2753168202" "Is that your belief, {HeroName}, that all villains should be judged harshly or not at all? If you believe that all villains should be judged harshly, then why should I give you the benefit of the doubt? Through your actions you are a villain, by your standards. You've become what you hate.<br><br>I'm sorry {HeroName}... you are clearly in need of help and headed down a dark and dangerous path. I cannot ignore or excuse what you have done. I'm going to have to take you in. It's for your own good. Please don't make this more difficult than it already is."
// Answer Text :
"P521076112" "Take me in? I'm trying to save your life and this is how you thank me!?"
// Page TeachingALesson4 Text :
"P2230805455" "I didn't want it to come to this, but you give me no choice. Defend yourself!"
// Answer Text :
"P651106868" "I'm going to kill you!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P4002738355" "The Lost have taken over an abandoned warehouse loaded with all kinds of advanced Rikti weaponry. You're hoping that such a dangerous group of murderous thugs will encourage Kuwalski to abandon his near suicidal practice of trying to apprehend and arrest several dozen armed super mutants by himself. Today, Kuwalski is going to learn that showing mercy to scum like The Lost just encourages them to attempt more and more sinister crimes. The only way to really deal with them is to deliver justice upon them then and there. After all, that's what they keep trying to do to you."
// AcceptString :
"P1696919634" "It's time Kuwalski learned how to fight crime... and kill it."
// SendOffString :
"P3593047352" "Officer Kuwalski has a lot of potential, but believes a little too much in the inherent good of others. There's only one person between life and death out here fighting crime in the streets, and that's you. If you're weak, you wind up dead, if you're strong, then evil perishes."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2226636504" "Teach Officer Kuwalski a lesson"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P359460316" "Find Kuwalski (hopefully he hasn't gotten himself killed) and then show him how ruthless he has to be to survive in this line of work."
// TaskTitle :
"P947425746" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Violent Cartoons, Moral Lessons</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2697519329" "Your communicator picks up a panicked burst from Officer Kuwalski. Sounds like he's gotten himself into trouble."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2294506755" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Violent Cartoons, Moral Lessons</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You saved Officer Kuwalski from certain torture and death at the hands of The Lost, told him what he needed to do to survive in this harsh reality, and he turned around and spit in your face. Even after giving him every chance, he had the gall to turn on you and call you a villain! You! A villain? Well, you showed him exactly what a villain would do to a weak willed fool like him, and now he's dead. The only saving grace of the entire despicable affair is that at least nobody got satisfaction out of killing a member of Longbow. Had The Lost done it, then it would have only encouraged them to kill more. With Kuwalski's blood on your hands it is just another reminder that the war against evil isn't over yet, and people are going to die. Lots of people."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P732667585" "You rescued Officer Kuwalski from The Lost. Try to convince him that mercy is a weakness."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P525796284" "Talk to Kuwalski"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P465236257" "With Kuwalski incapacitated you are free to express your criticism of his beliefs with him."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P124180548" "Talk To Kuwalski"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P398043990" "Explain Things To Kuwalski"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1642162788" "Beat down Kuwalski"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2029351575" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SteelBlue>If anyone can hear me, this is Officer Kuwalski of the Freedom Corps. I am surrounded by The Lost, they are very hostile. They have made it clear that they aim to take me captive. Over.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>I sense... {HeroName}. Now we have two test subjects for the Mind Probe! Come and save your friend. Refuse, and he will die!<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SteelBlue>They've got me cornered! Help! Anyone!?"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_NAME :
"P881596975" "Officer Kuwalski"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3100599471" "<shout><em t=1>Y... You're under arrest!"
// Script Variable CAPTOR_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3391115791" "<shout>Fight me, weakling!"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3375927186" "<shout><em t=3>Don't worry, {HeroName} is on {hero.gender=male his|her way}."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2807556874" "{HeroName}! Man, am I glad you got here when you did. The Lost said they were going to be moving some hitech equipment, we've gotta stop them before it's too late!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P550075280" "Wait, what are you doing? Ha ha, very funny {HeroName}... OWW! What are you doing!? Stop messing OWWWW! We need to destroy this, stop it! AAAAAGH! Please stop! You're seriously hurting me... I don't... feel... good."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3902987775" "No... NO! I won't do it, {HeroName}. I'll never sacrifice my moral values. Not like you have. Don't you see? You're just like them! The ends do not justify the means!"

